# Plan: Extract Service Layer from Route Handlers

## Context

The codebase is a TypeScript/Express.js API with two route files (`products.ts`, `orders.ts`) that mix HTTP concerns (request parsing, response sending) with business logic (filtering, aggregation, validation, state machines, stock mutation). The goal is to separate these concerns so route handlers only deal with HTTP, and all business rules live in a dedicated service layer. All existing integration tests must continue to pass unchanged.

---

## Final Directory Structure

```
src/
  app.ts                          (unchanged)
  data.ts                         (unchanged)
  types.ts                        (add new interfaces)
  errors.ts                       (NEW)
  routes/
    products.ts                   (refactored — HTTP only)
    orders.ts                     (refactored — HTTP only)
  services/
    product.service.ts            (NEW)
    order.service.ts              (NEW)
tests/
  products.test.ts                (unchanged)
  orders.test.ts                  (unchanged)
```

---

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1 — Create `src/errors.ts`

Single typed error class used by all services. Route handlers catch it and map to HTTP responses.

```typescript
export class ServiceError extends Error {
  constructor(public readonly statusCode: number, message: string) {
    super(message);
    this.name = "ServiceError";
  }
}
```

---

### Step 2 — Add view-model interfaces to `src/types.ts`

Append (do not modify existing interfaces):

```typescript
export interface ProductFilters {
  category?: string;
  minPrice?: number;
  maxPrice?: number;
}

export interface ProductListResult {
  products: Product[];
  summary: { count: number; totalInventoryValue: number; averagePrice: number };
}

export interface ProductDetail extends Product {
  isLowStock: boolean;
  inventoryValue: number;
}

export interface OrderFilters {
  userId?: number;
  status?: string;
}

export interface OrderListResult {
  orders: Order[];
  summary: { count: number; totalRevenue: number };
}

export interface EnrichedOrderItem extends OrderItem {
  productName: string;
}

export interface EnrichedOrder extends Omit<Order, "items"> {
  items: EnrichedOrderItem[];
}
```

---

### Step 3 — Create `src/services/product.service.ts`

Imports: `products` from `../data.js`, `ServiceError` from `../errors.js`, types from `../types.js`.

**`listProducts(filters: ProductFilters): ProductListResult`**
- Filter `products` array by `category` (exact match), `minPrice`, `maxPrice`
- Compute `totalInventoryValue = Σ(price × stock)` rounded to 2 dp
- Compute `averagePrice = Σ(price) / count` rounded to 2 dp (0 if empty)
- Return `{ products: filtered, summary: { count, totalInventoryValue, averagePrice } }`

**`getProductById(id: number): ProductDetail`**
- Find product; throw `new ServiceError(404, "Product not found")` if missing
- Return `{ ...product, isLowStock: stock < 10, inventoryValue: round(price × stock) }`

**`adjustProductStock(id: number, adjustment: number): ProductDetail`**
